§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ How many ways are there to arrange $n$ objects in order? ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ By the fundamental principle of counting, there are $n$ ways
    to select the first card, $n-1$ ways to select the second,
    and so on. ⦉

  ‖ Thus, the number of ways of stacking $n$ cards in a deck
    is
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ n(n-1)(n-2)⋯1 ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ We call this number the ❬factorial❭ of $n$, or
    ❬$n$-factorial❭. ⦉
⦉

